                        <title type="complete">Symbolical explanations of biblical passages</title> 
                        <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <note>Mainly symbolical explanations, called <foreign xml:lang="gez"/> of some biblical passages:
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1672Isaiah">Isaiah</ref> 4:1; 5:10; 7:8; 7:4; 19:18; 21:7; 23:15; 30:17; 34:15
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1671Isaiah">Ascension of Isaiah</ref>, 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3144Hosea">Za-Hoseʿ nabiyy</ref> 3:2; <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3146Micah">Za-Mikyās nabiyy</ref>, 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1689Joel">Book of Joel</ref>, <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3145Amos">Za-ʾAmoṣ nabiyy</ref>, 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1819Maccab">Maccabees, Book of (Ethiopic)</ref>, <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1376Apocal">Apocalypse of Ezra</ref>, 
                    Testament of the Apostles</note>
                        <quote xml:lang="gez">ኀሳብ፡ እምቃለ፡ ኪዳን፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወማቴዎስ ፤ ጴጥሮስ፡ ጸሐፍዎ፡ ለዝ፡ ኪዳን፡ እንዘ፡ ያጽሕፎሙ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ወፈነው፡ በአርኣያ፡
